{"id":131,"date":"2022-12-12T09:04:46","date_gmt":"2022-12-12T14:04:46","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/?p=131"},"modified":"2022-12-12T09:04:48","modified_gmt":"2022-12-12T14:04:48","slug":"commentary-in-wfmy2-may-2-2022","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/commentary-in-wfmy2-may-2-2022\/","title":{"rendered":"Commentary in WFMY2 May 2, 2022"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The tight supply and high prices associated with today&#8217;s housing market have some worried we may be nearing a housing bubble. On May 2, 2022, Alfredo Romero, an economics professor at North Carolina A&amp;T, said &#8220;current conditions don&#8217;t qualify as that. For a housing bubble to exist, we would have to believe some kind of story about the price rather than ignoring the economic fundamentals that cause the price of a house to be so high. In this case, I think the economic fundamentals justify the increasing prices we&#8217;ve seen.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" style=\"border:1px solid #e6e6e6\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wfmynews2.com\/embeds\/video\/responsive\/83-9f2b8076-ed4e-4447-8a00-dba17d7a2e80\/iframe\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"true\" mozallowfullscreen=\"true\"><\/iframe>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The tight supply and high prices associated with today&#8217;s housing market have some worried we may be nearing a housing bubble. On May 2, 2022,<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[11],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/131"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/alfredoromero.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v